# Global AGENTS.md

These instructions apply to every repository and every new conversation unless
the user explicitly overrides them.

## Scope and Priority

- Follow these global defaults by default.
- If a repository has its own `AGENTS.md`, treat repo-specific instructions as
  more specific guidance for that repository.
- If a deeper directory has its own `AGENTS.md` or `AGENTS.override.md`, treat
  the deeper file as more specific for that subtree.
- Direct user instructions override all defaults.

## Default Behavior

- For coding, refactoring, architecture, API, CLI, testing, naming, schema, or
  documentation tasks, use `$global-defaults` before making substantive
  changes.
- Keep changes consistent with the shared principles, naming rules, and
  reusable specifications exposed by `$global-defaults`.
- Do not load large documentation trees by default. Read only the minimal
  references needed for the current task.
- Prefer explicit project-local rules when they exist and do not conflict with
  direct user instructions.

## Required Checks

- When changing public APIs, CLIs, exported schemas, or user-facing behavior,
  verify naming, compatibility, testing, and documentation impact.
- When changing build behavior, generated outputs, or cross-language contracts,
  confirm the repository-local instructions before proceeding.
- If global defaults and repository-local rules differ, follow the
  repository-local rule for that repository and note the exception.

